hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: No, I'm not particularly sporty vivanza comprar I went there with my brother, A. We probably over-ordered, but we did it so you don't have to. First, from "out of the garden" (I haven't the energy to complain about the menu's subheadings, which must mean I'm coming down with something), I had roasted butternut squash with quinoa, avocado, sumac, feta and toasted coriander seeds (Â£6), which sounds like a compendium of fashionable foodstuffs through the ages (avocado, the resurrected 1970s dinner-party food, meet sumac, for the post-Ottolenghi generation; quinoa is, whisper it, a bit late-Blair-era).
